Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "brzinom":

1. *Brzinom* svetlosti, uspeo sam da izbegnem sudar sa drugim automobilom. (At the speed of light, I managed to avoid a collision with another car.)
2. Pretrčao je *brzinom* munje i pobedio u trci. (He ran at lightning speed and won the race.)
3. Ovaj automobil ide neverovatnom *brzinom*. (This car is going at an incredible speed.)
4. Ubrzanje letačkog aviona izražava se u *brzinama* koje se kreću od nekoliko stotina do nekoliko hiljada kilometara na sat. (The acceleration of an airplane is expressed in speeds ranging from several hundred to several thousand kilometers per hour.)
5. Moraš usporiti, jer voziš *brzinom* koja je iznad dozvoljene. (You need to slow down, because you're driving at a speed that's above the legal limit.)
6. *Brzinom* kojom se krećemo, stići ćemo na cilj za manje od sat vremena. (At the speed we're going, we'll reach the finish line in less than an hour.)

I hope these examples help!